cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper focuses on developing a modeling paradigm to augment predictive models of turbulence, which is a topic related to computational engineering. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper extensively uses machine learning techniques to reconstruct discrepancy information from a large number of inverse problems into corrective model forms. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses artificial intelligence techniques such as neural networks to reconstruct model forms. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural networks to reconstruct model forms. 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper deals with developing a modeling paradigm to improve the predictive capabilities of turbulent flows, which can be considered as a control problem.
